</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="g12">
<h3 style="color: #00533a; text-align: center;">Travel to the Lakes &amp; Mountains by rail</h3>
<p><img src="/media/13067834/inghams-lakes-and-mountains-rail-holidays-eurostar.jpg" alt="Eurostar to Europe with Inghams" data-udi="umb://media/65f5953b8b7c4ed6a72390d62de78d10" /></p>
<p>All our rail holidays depart London on Eurostar between 7am and 9am. And we include a Paris Metro ticket for your short hop between Paris Gard du Nord and your relevant Paris terminal.</p>
</div>
<div class="g4">
<h3 style="color: #00533a;">For Switzerland</h3>
<p><strong>Resorts:</strong> All resorts and multicentre holidays in <a data-udi="umb://document/92803bd348ec48c1b64d53e77931172d" href="/{localLink:umb://document/92803bd348ec48c1b64d53e77931172d}" title="Switzerland">Switzerland</a> </p>
<p><strong>Departures:</strong> Monday, Wednesday, Friday and Saturday</p>
<p><strong>Supplements (return) from:</strong> Standard Class £45; Standard Premier Class: £125</p>
<p>Travel from London to Paris on Eurostar and then on TGV to your resort, arriving between 6pm and 9pm the same day. Standard Premier Class includes travel on Eurostar and 1<sup>st</sup> class travel on TGV. If you wish to continue in first class on the Swiss rail network, an additional supplement of £35pp applies. In Standard Premier and 1<sup>st</sup> class TGV, meals and drinks are included appropriate to the time of day.</p>
</div>
<div class="g4">
<h3 style="color: #00533a;">For France</h3>
<p><strong>Resorts:</strong> <a data-udi="umb://document/59d85c3607bf4fc5a291361000fe9db0" href="/{localLink:umb://document/59d85c3607bf4fc5a291361000fe9db0}" title="Lake Annecy">Annecy</a> and Talloires</p>
<p><strong>Departures:</strong> Wednesday and Saturday</p>
<p><strong>Supplements (return) from:</strong> Standard Class £10; Standard Premier Class £60</p>
<p>Travel from Paris Gare de Lyon by TGV to Annecy arriving at approximately 5.30pm the same day. At Annecy a taxi will be waiting to take you to your hotel. Standard Premier Class includes travel on Eurostar and 1st class travel on TGV to Annecy. Meals and drinks are included on Standard Premier Class on the Eurostar only.</p>
</div>
<div class="g4">
<h3 style="color: #00533a;">For Italy</h3>
<p><strong>Resorts:</strong> <a data-udi="umb://document/40af41087b6c40cd950bbe672939b005" href="/{localLink:umb://document/40af41087b6c40cd950bbe672939b005}" title="Baveno">Baveno</a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/44b05c95e1264c56b51016621b99f80b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/44b05c95e1264c56b51016621b99f80b}" title="Stresa">Stresa</a> on <a data-udi="umb://document/476c8caf3fe84faab565f2d0f2e99f48" href="/{localLink:umb://document/476c8caf3fe84faab565f2d0f2e99f48}" title="Lake Maggiore">Lake Maggiore</a></p>
<p><strong>Departures:</strong> Wednesday and Saturday</p>
<p><strong>Supplements (return) from: </strong>Standard Class £45; Standard Premier Class from £125*</p>
<p>Travel from Paris Gare de Lyon by TGV to Geneva where you change trains for Stresa. Guests arrive in Lake Como at approximately 9.30pm and a taxi transfer to your hotel is included. Standard Premier Class includes travel by Eurostar from London to Paris and first class travel to your final rail stop. On the Eurostar and 1<sup>st</sup> class TGV, meals and drinks are included appropriate to the time of day.</p>
</div>
